# Section 0: CLI Runner Contract

This prompt is designed to run as a CLI under a future
`agent.code_reviewer.explainability_frontend` Python entry point. The runner
module is **MISSING_TODAY** — the section below is the spec the runner will
conform to. Until the runner ships, the prompt is invoked manually and the
`ReviewReport` JSON (Section 8) is hand-written by the agent.

## Invocation

```
python -m agent.code_reviewer.explainability_frontend \
    --files <comma_separated_paths_or_globs> \
    --scope <full|adapter_pr|ui_component_pr|wire_translator_pr|security_audit|sprint_audit> \
    --out <path/to/review.json> \
    [--fail-on <critical|warning|none>]
```

- `--files` accepts a comma-separated list of paths or glob patterns
  (e.g. `frontend-explainability/lib/adapters/**/*.ts,frontend-explainability/components/traces/WorkflowsTable.tsx`).
  When omitted, defaults to `git diff --name-only --diff-filter=ACMR origin/main...HEAD`.
- `--scope` selects which dimensions to evaluate. See Section 3 for the
  dimension catalogue (FD1-FD8) and `review_submission.j2` for the named
  scope → dimension mapping. Defaults to `full`.
- `--out` is the destination path for the structured `ReviewReport` JSON
  object (Section 8). Required. Pass `-` to emit JSON to stdout instead;
  in that case the human-readable `statement` is written to stderr.
- `--fail-on` decides the process exit code derived from the verdict.
  Defaults to `critical` (CI-friendly).

## Exit Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `0` | `verdict == "approve"` (or verdict is below the `--fail-on` threshold). |
| `1` | `verdict == "request_changes"` (or any warning when `--fail-on warning`). |
| `2` | `verdict == "reject"` (always non-zero, regardless of `--fail-on`). |
| `3` | Runner error (tool crash, unparseable file, missing baseline, prompt did not produce valid JSON). |

