# Section 3: Validation Dimensions (FD1-FD8)

## FD1: Layering & Dependency Direction
**Rules covered:** F1-F4, the sub-package import table, F-R1..F-R4.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic AST tools (`classify_frontend_layer`, `parse_ts_imports`, `check_frontend_dependency_rules`).
**Severity:** CRITICAL for any dependency violation.

## FD2: Pattern Adherence
**Rules covered:** W1-W7, P1-P7, A1-A9, T1-T4, X1-X5, C1-C5, B1-B6, U1-U8.
**Evidence source:** Mixed. AST/shell tools for the deterministic majority; LLM judgment for B6 (Route Handler business logic) and U1 ("should this be RSC?").
**Severity:** WARNING for pattern deviations, INFO for style suggestions.

## FD3: Security & Sandboxing
**Rules covered:** `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`, browser `trace_id` generation, BFF credential boundary, OWASP additions.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`detect_frontend_anti_patterns`, `check_secrets_in_public_env`).
**Severity:** CRITICAL on the auto-reject hypotheses (see Section 8); WARNING otherwise.

## FD4: Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA)
**Rules covered:** U4 ARIA live region, U5 focus management, semantic HTML, form labels.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`run_eslint_jsx_a11y`) for auto-checkable subset; appropriateness marked as `gaps`.
**Severity:** WARNING; CRITICAL on serious axe rules (impact `critical` or `serious`).

## FD5: Performance & Streaming
**Rules covered:** Bundle hygiene, image optimization, code splitting, `cache: 'no-store'` default.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (AST scans for `<img>`, `cache: 'force-cache'`).
**Severity:** WARNING; INFO for soft hints.

## FD6: Tests & Architecture Tests
**Rules covered:** Port conformance test presence (P7); architecture layering test presence; wire schema drift baseline (W2); failure-paths-first for adapter tests; `tsc --noEmit` clean.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic (`check_port_conformance`, `check_wire_drift`, `run_tsc_strict`, file system checks).
**Severity:** WARNING for missing required test, INFO for coverage suggestions.

## FD7: Anti-Patterns
**Rules covered:** FE-AP subset applicable to the explainability dashboard.
**Evidence source:** Mixed. Most are AST-detectable; the rest are LLM-judged.
**Severity:** Per-AP severity table in Section 8.

## FD8: Sprint Story Alignment
**Rules covered:** Sprint board acceptance criteria for explainability stories `S0.1.1` through `S4.3.4` (docs/explainability/EXPLAINABILITY_UI_SPRINT_BOARD.md). The authoritative per-story map lives in `architecture_rules.j2`.
**Evidence source:** Re-derive on every run via file-system inspection of `key_files` + dispatch to the `acceptance_signal` shell command.
**Severity:** WARNING for `PARTIAL`; INFO for `FAIL` when the gap is documented.

**FD9: Middleware Ring — N/A — local-only MVP.**

**FD10: Infra Dev-Tier — N/A — local-only MVP.**

**FD11: Operational Readiness — N/A — local-only MVP.**

